  "text": "Several mechanisms responsible for NSAIDS induced GI toxicity in general and in IBD patients specifically have been suggested. These include, increased mucosal permeability, formation of drugenterocyte adducts, and NSAIDS induced intracellular ATP deficiency and increased enterohepatic circulation. However, the most discussed mechanism is their effect on prostaglandin synthesis [CITATION_1] .",
